The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 11 December is 122,489 (14,117.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 06 December, there were 5,728 new confirmed cases (660.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 November, there were 5,600 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 2% (128 extra cases).
